properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 31 at 10:29PM EST until January 1 at 6:00AM EST by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC
properties.description:
* WHAT...Up to one foot of inundation above ground level in low
lying areas due to tidal flooding.

* WHERE...Shoreline in Southeast Harford County.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM EST Wednesday, especially around the time of
high tide.

* IMPACTS...At 4.5 feet, portions of the Havre de Grace Yacht
Basin are flooded, along with Hutchins Park.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Tides two and a half to three feet above
normal. The next high tide at Havre de Grace is 1:20 AM.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM EST WEDNESDAY
